wiki.summary: “Problematic” alternatively known as “Murder Murder” marks the fifteenth track of Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign’s Vultures. The song was first previewed on September 1, 2023, at Electric Picnic Festival in Dublin, Ireland where Ye previewed multiple unreleased songs to Steve Lacy backstage, including songs with Ty Dolla $ign and Young Thug. The song was played in full on February 8, 2024, at the Chicago Vultures Listening Party and again the following day at the New York Vultures Listening Party on February 9, 2024. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Problematic” alternatively known as “Murder Murder” marks the fifteenth track of Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign’s Vultures. The song was first previewed on September 1, 2023, at Electric Picnic Festival in Dublin, Ireland where Ye previewed multiple unreleased songs to Steve Lacy backstage, including songs with Ty Dolla $ign and Young Thug. The song was played in full on February 8, 2024, at the Chicago Vultures Listening Party and again the following day at the New York Vultures Listening Party on February 9, 2024. The track showcases Ye’s return to soul samples, a style of production popularised in his earlier projects such as The College Dropout. Throughout the track, Ye speaks on the backlash he faced following his controversial statements in late 2022 whilst bragging about his influence on the music and fashion worlds. Read more on Last.fm.
